<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-05-10T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-05-10T02:00:00-05:00" n="673" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d673">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.4731/102: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Sidney</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sydney</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-05-10T17:00:00+10:00">May
                                        10, 1934—5 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received May 11—5:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Before sending note as instructed have conferred with Trade
                                Commissioner and we both feel some uncertainty concerning
                                possibility of demonstrating that “American imports have suffered
                                greatly by the exception made in favor of Canada”, as stated in
                                second sentence of Department’s telegram of May 5, 2 p.m. It appears
                                to us that favor to Canada has not injured us very greatly, but has
                                merely relieved Canada of a disability imposed by basic Customs Act
                                from which we have suffered not only since but prior to the present
                                Canadian agreement.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>